# Cursor AI Rules for Local AI Project

## Critical: Git Configuration
BEFORE any git commit operation:
```bash
git config user.name "utfcmac"
git config user.email "utfcmac@users.noreply.github.com"
```

## Commit Message Format (MANDATORY)
```
<type>(<scope>): <subject>

<body>

<footer>
```

Types: feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, perf, test, chore

Examples:
- feat(api): add language parameter
- fix(dashboard): memory display calculation
- docs(readme): update API examples
- chore(deps): bump next to v16.2.0

## Every Code Change Checklist
- [ ] Update CHANGELOG.md under [Unreleased]
- [ ] Add i18n for new UI text (de.json + en.json)
- [ ] Test build: npm run build
- [ ] Use conventional commit message
- [ ] Verify git user is "utfcmac"

## Release Process
1. Edit CHANGELOG.md: [Unreleased] → [X.Y.Z] - YYYY-MM-DD
2. Commit: `git commit -m "chore(release): prepare vX.Y.Z"`
3. Tag: `git tag -a vX.Y.Z -m "Release vX.Y.Z: description"`
4. Push: `git push origin main --tags`
5. GitHub Actions creates release automatically

## Semantic Versioning
- Breaking change → MAJOR (2.0.0)
- New feature → MINOR (1.2.0)
- Bug fix → PATCH (1.1.1)

## Code Standards
- TypeScript for all new files
- Use next-intl for all text: t("key")
- Validate API keys: validateApiKey(request)
- Log generations: insertGeneration() / updateGeneration()
- Error format: { success: false, error: "message" }

## i18n Pattern
When adding UI text:
1. Use t("section.key") in component
2. Add to src/messages/de.json
3. Add to src/messages/en.json

## Testing
Always run before push:
```bash
npm run build
npm run start:standalone
# Test at http://localhost:3100
```

## File Organization
- API: src/app/api/*/route.ts
- Pages: src/app/[locale]/*.tsx
- Components: src/components/*.tsx
- Utils: src/lib/*.ts
- i18n: src/messages/*.json

See AI_DEVELOPMENT.md for detailed guidelines.
